      "message": "The bug is here.\n\n```\n-Dexperimental-redfish-multi-computer-system\u003ddisabled \\\n-Dredfish-dbus-log\u003ddisabled \\\n```\n\non Tyan S5549, truncate `/var/log/redfish` to contain only one EventLog entry.\n\n\n```\ncurl --silent --show-error --insecure --user root:**** https://s5549-bmc-a0423f63b4a5.lab.9e.network/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries\n{\n  \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries\",\n  \"@odata.type\": \"#LogEntryCollection.LogEntryCollection\",\n  \"Description\": \"Collection of System Event Log Entries\",\n  \"Members\": [\n    {\n      \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries/1775833843\",\n      \"@odata.type\": \"#LogEntry.v1_9_0.LogEntry\",\n      \"Created\": \"2026-04-10T15:10:43+00:00\",\n      \"EntryType\": \"Event\",\n      \"Id\": \"1775833843\",\n      \"Message\": \"PWS-920P-SQ PowerSupply with serial number P9212CM08UN1852 was installed.\",\n      \"MessageArgs\": [\n        \"PWS-920P-SQ\",\n        \"PowerSupply\",\n        \"P9212CM08UN1852\"\n      ],\n      \"MessageId\": \"OpenBMC.0.5.InventoryAdded\",\n      \"Name\": \"System Event Log Entry\",\n      \"Severity\": \"OK\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"Members@odata.count\": 1,\n  \"Name\": \"System Event Log Entries\"\n}\n```\n\nquerry again\n```\ncurl --silent --show-error --insecure --user root:***** https://s5549-bmc-a0423f63b4a5.lab.9e.network/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries\n{\n  \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries\",\n  \"@odata.type\": \"#LogEntryCollection.LogEntryCollection\",\n  \"Description\": \"Collection of System Event Log Entries\",\n  \"Members\": [\n    {\n      \"@odata.id\": \"/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries/1775833843_1\",\n      \"@odata.type\": \"#LogEntry.v1_9_0.LogEntry\",\n      \"Created\": \"2026-04-10T15:10:43+00:00\",\n      \"EntryType\": \"Event\",\n      \"Id\": \"1775833843_1\",\n      \"Message\": \"PWS-920P-SQ PowerSupply with serial number P9212CM08UN1852 was installed.\",\n      \"MessageArgs\": [\n        \"PWS-920P-SQ\",\n        \"PowerSupply\",\n        \"P9212CM08UN1852\"\n      ],\n      \"MessageId\": \"OpenBMC.0.5.InventoryAdded\",\n      \"Name\": \"System Event Log Entry\",\n      \"Severity\": \"OK\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"Members@odata.count\": 1,\n  \"Name\": \"System Event Log Entries\"\n}\n```\n\nnotice that \n`\"Id\": \"1775833843\"` has changed to `\"Id\": \"1775833843_1\"`\n\nThis is the bug where `Id` is incremented with each query.\n\nThe bug is also present when GET of single entry.\nThe `odata.id` returned from the event log collection is invalid since the static local variables in `getUniqueEntryID` has already changed.\n\nSo when fetching it, the previously returned link `/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/EventLog/Entries/1775833843_1` will not work for the redfish client.\n\n\n\nI only tested this patch, maybe the bug will go away with your other patch https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/89022",
